The improved lva of Section 2.6.3 is inter-procedural: it takes into account information that ﬂows between functions. Conversely, the basic lva presented in Section 2.6.1 is intra-procedural: it analyses the body of each function in isolation.

Summary The ﬁrst improvement for lva presented above is the use of function summaries: f ↓ is the summary of f . The following remarks apply.

