The value of Share( π )(x, p) is the certainty that p recognises two (or more) distinct sequences of dereference that, starting from the address of x, lead to the same memory cell at program point π for any execution. That is, Share( π )(z) indicates that at program point π , Z(z) has internal sharing in none (0), some (⊤) or all (1) of the executions.
As with Shape, this property is not decidable. As with Shape we accept approximations that are weaker (i.e., where ⊤ can appear in place of either 0 or 1).

